>[Question]
>In the equation t = 15s + 3 where s (speed) = cm/s (determining 
>temperature in Celcius using the speed & distance an ant can 
travel), 
>is cm/s centimeters per second?  
>
>[Difficulty]
>When we tested it, the temperature was unreasonable.
>
>[Thoughts]
>The ant traveled 82 cm in 5.87 seconds (to the best of our 
>calcualtions)  82/5.87 = 13.96 therefor t= 15 x 13.96 + 3
>
>t = 209.4 + 3
>t = 212.4
>That's mighty hot!!
